Gabadinho Mhango of Orlando Pirates celebrates goal with teammates during Absa Premiership match between Orlando Pirates and Black Leopards on 21 December 2019 at Orlando Stadium. JOHANNESBURG - Josef Zinnbauer began his era at Orlando Pirates with a 3-1 win over Black Leopards in an Absa Premiership match at the Orlando Stadium in Soweto on Saturday afternoon. Augustine Mulenga's goal gave The Buccaneers a 1-0 lead at half-time. READ: Carlo Ancelotti appointed Everton manager Leopards leveled matters in the second half, but Gabadinho Mhango promptly put the hosts back in the lead. Mhango converted a penalty to complete his brace and hand Pirates a convincing 3-1 win. The victory puts them level on 20 points with Highlands Park and Golden Arrows.